docs.snippet: BERLIN, March 24. -- The news that George S. Messersmith, American Consul General in Berlin, will go as United States Minister not to Uruguay but to Austria in succession to George H. Earle 3d, has greatly interested German official circles, in which...
docs.lead_paragraph: BERLIN, March 24. -- The news that George S. Messersmith, American Consul General in Berlin, will go as United States Minister not to Uruguay but to Austria in succession to George H. Earle 3d, has greatly interested German official circles, in which it is not too much to say it has aroused conflicting sentiments.
